                <p>Managing health challenges is key to keeping chickens healthy:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Coccidiosis:</strong> Regularly clean and disinfect the coop and provide medicated feed if necessary.</li>
                    <li><strong>Respiratory Infections:</strong> Ensure good ventilation and avoid overcrowding to prevent respiratory issues.</li>
                    <li><strong>Parasites:</strong> Implement a regular deworming and parasite control program.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Consult with a veterinarian for a tailored health management plan.</p>
            </div>
